  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Video-assisted thoracoscopic (VATs) lobectomy is mild to moderately pain procedure. For
      conventional thoracotomy, there are many invasive pain control such as epidural analgesia,
      paravertebral block. However, for VATs, the invasive pain control somehow are too invasive.
      Nefopam is non-opioid painkilling medication, Serotonin, norepinephrine, dopamine reuptake
      inhibitor. Many study were demonstrated positive outcome of nefopam usage in many operation
      such as abdominal surgery, laparocopic surgery, orthopedic surgery. Nevertheless, nefopam for
      VATs is not well studied yet.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
